\title{brapiR2: A Tidyverse-Native Client for the BrAPI v2 (Breeding API) Specification}
\description{
\if{html}{\figure{logo.png}{options: style='float: right' alt='logo' width='120'}}

Provides pipe-friendly, stateless access to every endpoint in the Breeding API (BrAPI) v2.1 specification. Covers all four BrAPI modules — Core, Germplasm, Phenotyping, and Genotyping — returning tidy tibbles ready for analysis. Features include automatic pagination, async search handling, response caching, parallel batch fetching, and convenience functions for genomic selection workflows (e.g. dosage matrix extraction). Designed for plant breeders and bioinformaticians who need programmatic access to BreedBase, BMS, EBS, GIGWA, Germinate, and any BrAPI-compliant server.
